A landmark Sufjan Stevens album springs to life onstage

Choreographer Justin Peck and playwright Jackie Sibblies Drury beautifully convey the story of ‘Illinoise’ through movement

March 7, 2024More than 1 year ago
5 min
Make us preferred on Google
Review by Gloria Oladipo

NEW YORK — The richness of Sufjan Stevens’s work feels at home on a stage. His 2007 project, “The BQE,” an ode to the Brooklyn-Queens Expressway, was a mixed-media exploration that debuted at the Brooklyn Academy of Music, complete with projections and synchronized hula-hoopers. Now, Stevens’s “Illinois” album is in three dimensions, thanks to a kaleidoscopic collaboration of movement, theater and music.
